names:  Spanish Manuel, Jose, Carlos, Jorge, Luis, Fernando, Gilberto, Mario, Ricardo, Augusto, Horacio, Joaquin.  Portuguese Joao, Joaquim, Agostinho, Catarina, Manoel, Paulo.","Portugese: from a short form of the Marian title and name <i>Maria das Neves</i> ‘Mary of the Snows’ (see   Nieves  ).","Galician and Asturian-Leonese: habitational name from any of the places called Neves in the provinces of Pontevedra, Lugo, and A Coruña (all three in Galicia), and Asturias."],"variants":[{"name":"Nieves","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Luis, Miguel, Carlos, Juan, Angel, Rafael, Francisco, Jesus, Luz, Manuel, Ramon.","Spanish: from a short form of the Marian title and name <i>María de las Nieves</i> ‘Mary of the Snows’, given particularly to children born on 5 August, on which date the Virgin allegedly once caused it to snow in Rome. The surname may also be a reference to a local church dedicated to the Virgin Mary bearing this title.","Spanish: possibly also a nickname from the plural of <i>nieve</i> ‘snow’, for someone with snow-white hair."]}]},{"name":"Mabille","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Elaborated form of   Mabel  , under the influence of the French phrase <i>ma belle</i> ‘my beautiful one’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Mabille De Lèves was born about 1165, in Lèves, Eure-et-Loir, Centre, France, her father, Milon de Lèves de Totes, was 41 and her mother, Berthe de Gisors d'Aumale, was 32. She married Guillaume III De Ferrières about 1185, in Lèves, Eure-et-Loir, Centre, France. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died before 1226, in Ferrières en Gâtinais, Loiret, Centre-Val de Loire, France."},"et":{"about 1165–before 1226":"umbes 1165–enne 1226","1165–1226":"1165–1226","1165–Male":"1165–Surnud","1190–1251":"1190–1251","1125–1201":"1125–1201","1134–1187":"1134–1187","before 1226":"enne 1226","1190":"1190","about 1190":"umb